{"questionId":"20914","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Particle A travels in a straight line such that its displacement, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi></math> metres, from a fixed origin&nbsp;after <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds is given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>10</mn></math>, as shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/02915798495d49d6a9e8f1a26608c8f79648d79a.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Particle A starts at the origin and passes through the origin again when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Particle A changes direction when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The total distance travelled by particle A is given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn></math> forward <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>36</mn></math> backward&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>20</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munderover><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mn>10</mn></munderover><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>v</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>52</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mtext>m</mtext></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20914","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.9d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of d.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.9—Kinematics problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}